  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Mary H. Colman intended to send Deborah Weston a longer letter, but she has three more letters to write in school. She is going to see the doctor about her head and fears that she may have to stay home from school two or three days. She complains of the heat. She says that &quot;all the scholars send their love to you and yours.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Also includes a sheet of paper that was once folded and used as an envelope. It has the delivery address: Miss D. Weston, Weymouth.</subfield>
